    "plan_content": "The plan is complete. Here's a summary of what was researched and designed:\n\n---\n\n## What Was Explored\n\n- **All IRC plugin files** (`extensions/irc/` — 36 files) — the primary reference, read in full\n- **Nostr plugin** (`extensions/nostr/`) — pattern for non-core channel plugins\n- **Matrix plugin** — another non-core extension comparison\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/irc.ts`** — maps every symbol used by IRC's `runtime-api.ts` to its canonical public SDK path\n- **`scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json`** — all 143 public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` subpaths\n- **`channel-inbound`, `channel-pairing`, `runtime-group-policy`, `security-runtime`, `channel-lifecycle`, `channel-setup`, `status-helpers`** SDK path contents\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings & Design Decisions\n\n**22 files** in `extensions/pulseboard/` only — nothing else touched.\n\n**PulseBoard domain:**\n- Board targets use `$board-name` prefix (dollar sign), DMs use plain `username`\n- Env vars: `PULSEBOARD_HOST`, `PULSEBOARD_TOKEN`, `PULSEBOARD_USERNAME`, `PULSEBOARD_BOARDS`\n- `configured = host && token && username` (all three required)\n\n**Critical architectural note — `runtime-api.ts`:** Because PulseBoard is not a core channel, there is no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` facade. Unlike IRC (which uses `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`) or Nostr (`openclaw/plugin-sdk/nostr`), the PulseBoard barrel must re-export each symbol from its **actual** public SDK subpath directly.\n\n**Inbound dispatch split:** `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` is private to `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`. PulseBoard uses `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime` (public in `channel-inbound`) for DMs, and the `PluginRuntime`'s `core.channel.*` APIs directly for group/board dispatch.\n\n**Setup surface:** Uses `createOptionalChannelSetupSurface` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-setup` — the correct pattern for non-core bundled extensions (same as Nostr).",
